{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"2331","heading":"Use of continuing contracts for construction of certain projects","label":"2331 Use of continuing contracts for construction of certain projects","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2331","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/ch36/schV","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2331","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","CodificationSection was enacted as part of the Water Resources Development Act of 1999, and not as part of the Water Resources Development Act of 1986 which comprises this chapter.","Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","“Secretary” DefinedSecretary means the Secretary of the Army, see , set out as a note under .section 2 of Pub. L. 106–53section 2201 of this title"],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":"In general","label":"a In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2331/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2331","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2331%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Notwithstanding any other provision of law, the Secretary shall not implement a fully allocated funding policy with respect to a water resource project if initiation of construction has occurred but sufficient funds are not available to complete the project.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":"Continuing contracts","label":"b Continuing contracts","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2331/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t33/s2331","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft33%2Fs2331%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Secretary shall enter into a continuing contract for a project described in subsection (a).","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsec